utant general, shall design combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, and combat medical badge distinguishing processed emblems. Upon receipt of two hundred fifty orders for combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, or combat medical badge special registration plates, accompanied by a start-up fee of twenty dollars per order, the department shall begin issuing special registration plates with the applicable distinguishing processed emblem as provided in paragraphs }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, and }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fd\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The minimum order requirement shall apply separately to each of the special registration plates created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who was awarded a combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, or combat medical badge by the United States government may, upon written application to the department and presentation of satisfactory proof of the award, order special registration plates with a combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, or combat medical badge processed emblem. The special plate fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the annual validation of letter-number designated combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, and combat medical badge plates, and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the issuance and annual validation of personalized combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, and combat medical badge plates shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the veterans license fee fund created in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 35A.11}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ the amount of the special fees collected under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, in the previous month for combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, and combat medical badge plates.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Notwithstanding }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, an owner who is approved for special registration plates under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be issued one set of special registration plates with a combat infantryman badge, combat action badge, combat action ribbon, air force combat action medal, or combat medical badge distinguishing processed emblem at no charge.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The surviving spouse of a person who was issued special plates under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ may continue to use or apply for and use the special plates subject to registration of the special plates in the surviving spouse\u8217\'3fs name and upon payment of the annual five-dollar special plate fee and the regular annual registration fee for the vehicle. If the surviving spouse remarries, the surviving spouse shall return the special plates to the department and the department shall issue regular registration plates to the surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{21.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E34_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E34_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Iowa heritage special plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ may, upon written application to the department, order special registration plates with an Iowa heritage emblem. The emblem shall contain a picture of the American gothic house and the words \u8220\'3fIowa Heritage\u8221\'3f and shall be designed by the department in consultation with the state historical society of Iowa.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The special Iowa heritage fee for letter-number designated plates is thirty-five dollars. The special fee for personalized Iowa heritage plates is twenty-five dollars which shall be paid in addition to the special fee of thirty-five dollars. The annual special Iowa heritage fee is ten dollars for letter-number designated registration plates and is fifteen dollars for personalized registration plates which shall be paid in addition to the regular annual registration fee.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The special fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall credit monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the Iowa heritage fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 8A.709}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ the amount of the special fees collected in the previous month for the Iowa heritage plates.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{22.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E35_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E35_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Education plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, upon written application to the department, may order special registration plates with an education emblem. The education emblem shall be designed by the department in cooperation with the department of education.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The special school transportation fee for letter-number designated education plates is thirty-five dollars. The fee for personalized education plates is twenty-five dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the special school transportation fee of thirty-five dollars. The annual special school transportation fee is ten dollars for letter-number designated registration plates and is fifteen dollars for personalized registration plates which shall be paid in addition to the regular annual registration fee. The fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the school budget review committee in accordance with }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 257.31, subsection 17}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the amount of the special school transportation fees collected in the previous month for the education plates.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{23.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E36_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E36_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Breast cancer awareness plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Upon application and payment of the proper fees, the director may issue breast cancer awareness plates to an owner of a motor vehicle referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Breast cancer awareness plates shall contain an image of a pink ribbon and shall be designed by the department in consultation with the Susan G. Komen foundation.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The special fee for letter-number designated breast cancer awareness plates is thirty-five dollars. The fee for personalized breast cancer awareness plates is twenty-five dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the special breast cancer awareness fee of thirty-five dollars. The fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the department of health and human services the amount of the special fees collected in the previous month for the breast cancer awareness plates and such funds are appropriated to the department of health and human services. The department of health and human services shall distribute one hundred percent of the funds received monthly in the form of grants to support breast cancer screenings for both men and women who meet eligibility requirements like those established by the Susan G. Komen foundation. In the awarding of grants, the department of health and human services shall give first consideration to affiliates of the Susan G. Komen foundation and similar nonprofit organizations providing for breast cancer screenings at no cost in Iowa. Notwithstanding }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 8.33}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, moneys transferred under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not revert to the general fund of the state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Upon receipt of the special registration plates, the applicant shall surrender the current registration plates to the county treasurer. The county treasurer shall validate the special registration plates in the same manner as regular registration plates are validated under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The annual special breast cancer awareness fee for letter-number designated plates is ten dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the regular annual registration fee. The annual special fee for personalized breast cancer awareness plates is five dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the annual special breast cancer awareness fee and the regular annual registration fee. The annual special breast cancer awareness fee shall be credited and transferred as provided under paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{24.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E37_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E37_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Gold star plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who is the surviving spouse, parent, child, or sibling of a deceased member of the United States armed forces who died while serving on active duty during a time of military conflict or who died as a result of such service may order special registration plates bearing a gold star emblem upon written application to the department accompanied by satisfactory supporting documentation as determined by the department. The gold star emblem shall be designed by the department in cooperation with the commission of veterans affairs. The special plate fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the annual validation of letter-number designated gold star plates, and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the issuance and annual validation of personalized gold star plates shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the veterans license fee fund created in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 35A.11}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ the amount of the special fees collected under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, in the previous month for gold star plates.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Notwithstanding }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, an owner who is approved for special registration plates under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be issued one set of special registration plates bearing a gold star emblem at no charge.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{25.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E38_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E38_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Civil war sesquicentennial plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The department, in consultation with the adjutant general, shall design a civil war sesquicentennial distinguishing processed emblem. Upon receipt of two hundred fifty orders for civil war sesquicentennial special registration plates, accompanied by a start-up fee of twenty dollars per order, the department shall begin issuing special registration plates with a civil war sesquicentennial processed emblem as provided in paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, upon written application to the department, may order special registration plates with a civil war sesquicentennial processed emblem. The special plate fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraphs }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the issuance and annual validation of letter-number designated and personalized civil war sesquicentennial plates shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the department of administrative services the amount of the special fees collected under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, in the previous month for civil war sesquicentennial plates, and such funds are appropriated to the department of administrative services to be used for the Iowa battle flag project.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{26.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E39_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E39_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Fallen peace officers plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The department, in consultation with the department of public safety and concerns of police survivors, inc., shall design a fallen peace officers distinguishing processed emblem. Upon receipt of two hundred fifty orders for fallen peace officers special registration plates, accompanied by a start-up fee of twenty dollars per order, the department shall begin issuing special registration plates with a fallen peace officers processed emblem as provided in paragraphs }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner of a motor vehicle referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, upon written application to the department, may order special registration plates with a fallen peace officers processed emblem. The special fee for letter-number designated fallen peace officers plates is thirty-five dollars. The fee for personalized fallen peace officers plates is twenty-five dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the special fallen peace officers fee of thirty-five dollars. The fees collected by the director under this paragraph shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the department of public safety the amount of the special fees collected in the previous month for the fallen peace officers plates and such funds are appropriated to the department of public safety. The department of public safety shall distribute one hundred percent of the funds received monthly in the form of grants to nonprofit organizations that provide resources to assist in the rebuilding of the lives of surviving families and affected coworkers of law enforcement officers killed in the line of duty. In the awarding of grants, the department of public safety shall give first consideration to concerns of police survivors, inc., and similar nonprofit organizations providing such resources. Notwithstanding }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 8.33}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, moneys transferred under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not revert to the general fund of the state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Upon receipt of the special registration plates, the applicant shall surrender the current registration plates to the county treasurer. The county treasurer shall validate the special registration plates in the same manner as regular registration plates are validated under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The annual special fallen peace officers fee for letter-number designated plates is ten dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the regular annual registration fee. The annual special fee for personalized fallen peace officers plates is five dollars, which shall be paid in addition to the annual special fallen peace officers fee and the regular annual registration fee. The annual special fallen peace officers fee shall be credited and transferred as provided under paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{27.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E47_2E4_30_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E47_2E4_30_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{United States veteran plates.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An owner referred to in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who served in the armed forces of the United States and was discharged under honorable conditions may, upon written application to the department and upon presentation of satisfactory proof of military service and discharge under honorable conditions, order special registration plates bearing a distinguishing processed emblem depicting the word \u8220\'3fveteran\u8221\'3f below an image of the American flag. The application is subject to approval by the department. The special plate fees collected by the director under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the annual validation of letter-number designated United States veteran plates, and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, from the issuance and annual validation of personalized United States veteran plates, shall be paid monthly to the treasurer of state and deposited in the road use tax fund. The treasurer of state shall transfer monthly from the statutory allocations fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.145, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to the veterans license fee fund created in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 35A.11}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ the amount of the special fees collected under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, in the previous month for United States veteran plates.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Notwithstanding }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, an owner who is approved for a special registration plate under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be issued one set of special registration plates bearing a distinguishing processed emblem depicting the word \u8220\'3fveteran\u8221\'3f below an image of the American flag at no charge.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[SS15, \'a71571-m5; C24, 27, 31, 35, \'a74874; C39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{5001.18;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7321.34}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{82 Acts, ch 1032, \'a72, 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 82 Acts, ch 1062, \'a74, 38}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 84 Acts, ch 1027, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 84 Acts, ch 1250, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 84 Acts, ch 1305, \'a749}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 85 Acts, ch 67, \'a735}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 85 Acts, ch 87, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 86 Acts, ch 1182, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 86 Acts, ch 1225, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 87 Acts, ch 77, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 88 Acts, ch 1215, \'a71 \u8211\'3f 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 88 Acts, ch 1222, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 17, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 27, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 247, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 296, \'a727}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 317, \'a731}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 90 Acts, ch 1128, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 90 Acts, ch 1151, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 91 Acts, ch 49, \'a71, 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 91 Acts, ch 58, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 91 Acts, ch 259, \'a73}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 92 Acts, ch 1175, \'a729}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/acts//CH0000.pdf" }{\fldrslt \f5 \fs18{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\cf5{92 Acts, 2nd Ex, ch 1001, \'a7204, 205}}}}}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 93 Acts, ch 2, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 94 Acts, ch 1104, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 95 Acts, ch 118, \'a77 \u8211\'3f 9, 40}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 96 Acts, ch 1065, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 96 Acts, ch 1088, \'a73, 4, 8}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 96 Acts, ch 1171, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 96 Acts, ch 1219, \'a721 \u8211\'3f 24}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 2, \'a71, 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 70, \'a73, 15}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 104, \'a78 \u8211\'3f 10}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 108, \'a75}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 123, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 212, \'a733}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 98 Acts, ch 1079, \'a71 \u8211\'3f 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 99 Acts, ch 7, \'a71 \u8211\'3f 9}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 99 Acts, ch 114, \'a720}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 99 Acts, ch 141, \'a738}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 99 Acts, ch 180, \'a715}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2000 Acts, ch 1154, \'a721}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2000 Acts, ch 1157, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2000 Acts, ch 1206, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2001 Acts, ch 24, \'a773, 74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2001 Acts, ch 32, \'a717}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2001 Acts,